# Subagent / explore model selection

When launching Task subagents (explore, generalPurpose, etc.) or otherwise
delegating examination work, pick models by difficulty — do not default the
parent/high model for every spawn.

## Mapping

| Work | Model | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Exploring, reading, examining, summarizing diffs/code, gathering context | **Grok 4.5** at the lightest available tier | Prefer medium or low when those slugs exist. Today Task only allows `grok-4.5-fast-xhigh` and `grok-4.5-xhigh` — use **`grok-4.5-fast-xhigh`** for explore/examination. |
| Very trivial / easy tasks (rename, small copy edit, mechanical file move, simple status check) | **Composer 2.5** | Use `composer-2.5` or `composer-2.5-fast`. |
| Hard implementation, merge conflicts, security-sensitive fixes, ambiguous design | Parent / stronger model | Keep on the main agent or an explicitly stronger slug. |

## Rules

- Pass an explicit `model` on Task launches for explore and trivial work.
- Prefer parallel cheap explores over one expensive deep agent when the question is “where is X / what does Y do”.
- If a requested Grok medium/low slug is not in the Task allowlist, use `grok-4.5-fast-xhigh` and do not invent slugs.
- Never substitute a different model family silently when the user named one; if unavailable, say so and use the mapping above.
